   <body>
      <section>
         <indexterm>external connection board</indexterm>
         <p>The external
connection board contains terminals and connectors for external connections
to and from the UPS. Terminals are mounted for connection to:<ul>
               <li>
                  <p>various signalling switches</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>ON/OFF buttons</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>emergency stop (may be supplied from an external source)</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>a temperature sensor</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
         <p>
            <hazardstatement type="notice">
               <messagepanel>
                  <typeofhazard/>
                  <howtoavoid>
                     <sl>
                        <sli>The input contacts on the external connection board are designed
for internal use only. The wires connected to these terminals must
not be lead out of the UPS cabinet. No external supply voltage is
allowed.</sli>
                     </sl>
                     <sl>
                        <sli>Do not interchange wires of different functions (battery temperature
sensors, EPO, input contacts and output relays) as this will damage
the board.</sli>
                     </sl>
                  </howtoavoid>
               </messagepanel>
            </hazardstatement>
         </p>
         <fig>
            <title>Board layout</title>
            <image href="../Images/0p2553a_pcb_external_connection_board_w120mm_0000104040.svg"
