      </section>
      <section>
         <title>Input Contacts and Output Relays</title>
         <p>Summary
of signals:<ul>
               <li>
                  <p>1 common alarm output relays</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>2 free programmable output relays</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>1 EPO input contact</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>2 free programmable inputs contacts</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>1 battery temperature input and/or ambient temperature (free
programmable)</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
      </section>
      <section>
         <title>Assignment</title>
         <p>All of the input contacts and
output relays can be assigned to functions and alarms by configuration
(no fixed assignments). The Emergency Power OFF (EPO) is an exception
as it is always assigned as shown in the connection diagram for the
external connection board. There are two connection options:</p>
